Under the current implementation, Swift is not good at inferring types when some generic or overloaded functions (including operators) are used in combination.

So, this would improve the compile time:
```
func molasses(x:Double) -&gt; Double {
    let f = floor(x * 3) * 2
    let a = abs(x * 6 - f - 1)
    return 1 - a
}
```
(You may think this as sort of _cluttering up_...)

Or, using some type-specific (non-generic, non-overloaded) functions would do as well:
```
func dfloor(_ x: Double)-&gt;Double {floor(x)}

func molasses(x:Double) -&gt; Double {
    return 1 - fabs(x * 6 - dfloor(x * 3) * 2 - 1)
}
```

